<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the President’s
                                Special Assistant</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d433fn1">Sent to Cairo via Army channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-03">December 3, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> left here yesterday
                            morning. I am therefore sending him message through Soviet Embassy here
                            containing information in your <pb facs="0771" n="667" xml:id="pg_667"/>
                            cable to me<note n="2" xml:id="d433fn2"><persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName>’ telegram of December 2, 1943, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_605">p.
                                605</ref>.</note> but as time is so short believe you should also
                            have appropriate person in Algiers inform <persName corresp="#p_VAY1">Vyshinsky</persName> and offer him air transportation to Cairo.
                                <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> stated in Tehran that
                            he would designate <persName corresp="#p_VAY1">Vyshinsky</persName> to
                            represent the Soviet Government at the conference.<note n="3" xml:id="d433fn3">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_580">pp. 580</ref>–<ref target="#pg_590">590</ref>.</note> I have advised <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> of the probability of your placing plane at
                                <persName corresp="#p_VAY1">Vyshinsky</persName> disposal in Algiers
                            in the event he still desires him to attend conference.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>